    <item>
      <title>PackChat: Motorcycle intercom app I needed and built</title>
      <link>https://cr0wn-gh0ul.github.io/Cr0wn-Gh0ul/posts/2026-03-26/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://cr0wn-gh0ul.github.io/Cr0wn-Gh0ul/posts/2026-03-26/</guid>
      <description>Overview My wife and I run Cardo Freecom 2Xs. One friend has Sena. Another guy has some random Amazon special. And the next rider who shows up will probably bring something else entirely. That is exactly why PackChat exists. I did not build it to start a comms company. I built it because real ride groups are messy in the most normal way possible:&#xA;mixed brands mixed budgets mixed generations of hardware zero chance everyone is throwing away perfectly good gear just to match one stack That is the gap.</description>
